&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;





We have a fantastic opportunity for an enthusiastic GP to join our team.
 

&lt;p&gt;You will undertake a variety of duties including face to face and  telephone consultations, home visits, checking and signing repeat prescriptions along with dealing with queries, reports and paperwork. As expected your working day will encompass  all the general duties and responsibilities associated with a GP working within a primary care environment.&lt;/p&gt;
For further information please contact Rebecca Pittuck on 01245 260459 or by email rebecca.pittuck@nhs.net
 

&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close this vacancy early if we receive a large number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

No Agencies
 







&lt;strong&gt;About The Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;






 You must have :

&lt;p&gt;• Full GMC Registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Be a qualified GP, and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Currently be on the performers list without ever having been removed for a detrimental reason.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;







&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;






&lt;p&gt;Chelmer Medical Partnership is a friendly and supportive 28,000 patient partnership with 6 Partners based in Chelmsford Essex. We are a training practice operating across three sites.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We play an active role in our local PCN and have excellent clinical, admin and management support teams to support you in your role.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can offer 6 weeks annual leave plus 1 week study leave (pro-rata depending on sessions agreed) with your salary to be discussed at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
